reviews.review: The movie was very good. The story line was kind of week.
The ultimate middle finger to The Last Jedi...I loved that!
Stunning visuals, plus some new and old planets! I felt it lacked the slow pace of previous Star Wars movies, it felt a little rushed. But other than that it was a great conclusion to the saga!

After going to see this movie and listening to the critics talk about the movie. I had certain lower expectations of the movie then I may be have had going into any Star Wars movie. After seeing the movie I can honestly say it is a very good movie. Now is it the best Star Wars movie probably not. The movie is filled with action and the pace is very good. Though it had a lot of stuff in it because Abrams had the make up for the miss steps of the previous movie the last jedi. He essentially had to create 2 movies and fit them into one but he did a good job at this. Though it didn't flow seamlessly and there is quite a bit of fan service in the movie to the casual Star Wars fan they will not notice. The hardcore fans by no means got everything they wanted in this movie and it didn't go far enough but over all the movie itself is a really good film. It's fun and enjoyable and it is worth going to see.

It was amazing! J. J. Abrams had his work cut out for him to get this story back on track. He did a fantastic job creating something the fans could identify as a Star Wars creation. I loved it and could accept his vision easily.
True to the spirit of Star Wars

The movie is a fun time. The humor works well and the action was well done.

Thematically inconsistent and disrespectful to The Last Jedi, it's an incompetent and ideologically distant film that seems like it's making it up as it goes along. A disappointing conclusion the the decades-long Skywalker saga. What was the point?
A fitting, emotional and action packed end! Amazing movie, the best since empire! Thank you JJ!!
It was surprisingly funny, fast and not stop action movie.There was some emotionally moments and much better character performance and directions than the episode 8 for me.

I loved it and don’t understand the criticism. I thought it tied all of the elements together from the prior movies. None of the films have been able to find an actor with the swagger and charisma of Harrison Ford, but that’s a small criticism.
